#!/bin/bash

# This bash file executes operations to setup vim as a c++ IDE. You can find information of different setup methods here:
# https://idorobotics.com/2018/04/01/setting-up-vim-for-c-development/

# (1) At first install a plugin manager using one of the following tutorials:
# https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2prsFrKwbOo&t=313s
# https://opensource.com/article/20/2/how-install-vim-plugins

# (2) Install the NERDTree plugin to get a navigation for files: 
# IMPORTANT: If there is an error saying: 
# File "/usr/lib/python2.7/dist-packages/pip/basecommand.py", line 215, in main ... try the following to solve the 
# problem:
# sudo python -m pip install --upgrade --force setuptools
# sudo python -m pip install --upgrade --force pip

# Install project management plugin
sudo pip install local_vimrc 

# Install C++ Code editing

